   @{i}Windows:@{ui}
      @{" Main window       " link "WI_Main" 0}
      @{" Filter window     " link "WI_Filter" 0}
      @{" Search window     " link "WI_Search" 0}
      @{" Category window   " link "WI_Category" 0}
      @{" Program window    " link "WI_Prog" 0}
      @{" Disk choice window" link "WI_Disk" 0}
      @{" Process window    " link "WI_Process" 0}
      @{" Edit disks window " link "WI_EditDisks" 0}
      @{" Rename disk window" link "WI_NameDisk" 0}

   @{i}Menus:@{ui}
      @{" Project           " link "Menu_Project" 0}
      @{" Edit              " link "Menu_Edit" 0}
      @{" Settings          " link "Menu_Settings" 0}
@endnode

@node "WI_Main" "Main window"
@toc "Reference"

   This is the main window of PDBase. From there, you can navigate in your
   database, search a program, or edit this database.

   @{b}Browse/Edit (page gadget):@{ub}
      Selects PDBase mode:
         Browse mode allows you to search a program in the database.
         Edit mode allows you to edit your database.

   @{b}Left listview:@{ub}
      Lists the programs and categories included in the current category.

   @{b}Text below:@{ub}
      Shows the current category.

   @{b}Parent:@{ub}
      Goes to parent category.

   @{b}Root:@{ub}
      Goes to root (main) category.

   @{b}Rigth listviews:@{ub}
      If a program is selected in the left listview, shows the version,
         when the program was last modified, the files composing the program,
         and the comment.


   @{i}In Browse mode:@{ui}

      @{b}Filter...:@{ub}
         Opens the @{"filter window" link WI_Filter}.

      @{b}Active:@{ub}
         Activate or desactivate the filter. If filter is on, programs
            rejected by the filter will not be displayed.

      @{b}Recursive:@{ub}
         Sets recursive mode of the filter. If the filter is in recursive
            mode, a category will be displayed only if at least one program
            of this category (or of a sub-category) is accepted by the filter.
            If recursive mode is off, categories will always be displayed.

      @{b}Search...:@{ub}
         Opens the @{"search window" link WI_Search}

      @{b}Next:@{ub}
         Goes to the next program that matches search requirements.

      @{b}Previous:@{ub}
         Goes to the previous program that matches search requirements.


   @{i}In Edit mode:@{ui}

      @{b}Add Program:@{ub}
         Adds a new program to the database.

      @{b}Add Category:@{ub}
         Adds a new category to the database.

      @{b}Edit:@{ub}
         Edit selected programs and categories.

      @{b}Remove:@{ub}
         Remove selected programs and categories.

      @{b}Move to Temp:@{ub}
         Move selected program and categories to temporary buffer.
            Note: you can't save a base when the temp buffer is not empty.

      @{b}Move From Temp:@{ub}
         Move programs and categories in temporary buffer into current
            category.

@endnode

@node "WI_Filter" "Filter window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window allows you to select which programs will be rejected by the
      filter.

   The filter can reject programs that have been changed before a date, or
      after another.

      @{b}Before@{ub}:
         If the checkmarck is checked, all programs changed before the date
            entered in the string gadget will be rejected.

      @{b}After@{ub}:
         If the checkmarck is checked, all programs changed after the date
            entered in the string gadget will be rejected.
@endnode

@node "WI_Search" "Search window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window allows you to specify the search requirements.

      @{b}Search:@{ub}
        The pattern PDBase will search for. All amigados jokers are
            allowed.

      @{b}In Category:@{ub}
         Shows the category the search is restrained to when in
            "selected category" search mode.
            The popup gadget is used to select the category.

      @{b}Next:@{ub}
         Goes to the next program that matches search requirements.

      @{b}Previous:@{ub}
         Goes to the previous program that matches search requirements.

      @{b}Name/File/Link/Comment (checkmarks):@{ub}
         Selects which field(s) are compared to the pattern you gave.

      @{b}Selected category/Whole database:@{ub}
         Selects whether the search occurs in the whole database or in
            a specified category.
@endnode



@node "WI_Category" "Category window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window opens when you add a new category or edit an old one.
   It contains all the parameters describing this category.

   @{b}Path:@{ub}
      Shows the category where the edited category is located.

   @{b}Name:@{ub}
      Name of the edited category.
@endnode

@node "WI_Prog" "Program window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window opens when you add a new program or edit an old one.
   It contains all the parameters describing this program.


   @{b}Category:@{ub}
      Shows the category where the edited program is located.

   @{b}Name:@{ub}
      Name of the edited program.

   @{b}Version:@{ub}
      Version of the edited program.

   @{b}Comment:@{ub}
      Comment of the edited program.

   @{b}Files listview:@{ub}
      Shows the files composing the program.

      * A disk icon in front of a file shows that this is a FILE.

      * A Harddisk icon in front of a file shows that this is a LINK.

      * The letter "N" in front of a file shows that this file is New
         (not yet added to a disk). You can select the destination disk
         for this file with a double-click on the file.

      * The letter "D" in front of a file shows that this file is marked
         as Deleted, i.e it will be deleted as soon as possible.

   @{b}Add File:@{ub}
      Adds new file(s). Opens a file-requester for you to choose this(these)
         file(s). This file will be assigned a default destination disk.
         You can change it by double-clicking on the file.

   @{b}Delete source:@{ub}
      With this cycle gadget, you can decide wether a source file will be
         deleted after copy. "Ask" means that PDBase will ask you what to do
         with the source file after each copy.

   @{b}Add Link:@{ub}
      Adds new link(s). Opens a file-requester for you to choose this(these)
         file(s).

   @{b}Remove:@{ub}
      Removes the selected file.

   @{b}Restore:@{ub}
      Restores the selected files.

@endnode

@node "WI_Disk" "Disk choice window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window lets you choose the destination disk for a file.

   @{b}File:@{ub}
      Name of the file you're going to add.

   @{b}Size:@{ub}
      Size of the file you're going to add.

   @{b}Listview:@{ub}
      Use it to select the destination disk for the new file.

      * A disk that seems not to have enough space for this file is shown
         in black.

      * A disk that seems to have enough space for this file is shown in
         white.

      * The first disk: <New Disk> is special: it allows you to add a new
         disk to the database and assign the file to this new disk.
@endnode

@node "WI_Process" "Process window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window opens to show you what is happening when PDBase processes
   some files.

   Sometimes, you will be asked a question, and one or more buttons will
      appear. Just read the text in the listview and answer to the question,
      the text should be self-explanatory.


   When PDBase asks you if you want to delete the source file after the copy,
      two different situations can happen:
   * if this is the last file that PDBase has to copy in this program: two
      gadgets appear: "Delete" and "Continue".
   * if there are more files to copy after this one in this program, two
      additionnal gadgets appear: "All" and "None". "All" means that the
      all source files of this program will be deleted after being copied.
      "None" means that none of the source files of this program will be
      deleted after copy.
      "Delete" and "Continue" delete/don't delete the current source file, and
      will ask the same question for the next file.
@endnode

@node "WI_EditDisks" "Edit disks window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window shows you the list of known disks (i.e. used by PDBase to
store your files) and the list of the files stored on each disk.

   @{i}Left Listview:@{ui}
      You can use @{b}Drag&Drop@{ub} to sort the disks in this list

      @{b}Sort:@{ub}
         Sorts the disks in alphabetical order.

      @{b}Listview:@{ub}
         Displays the list ok known disks, and has two colums,
            column 1: name of the disk.
            column 2: estimated free size on this disk.

      @{b}Add:@{ub}
         Adds a new disk to the list.

      @{b}Remove:@{ub}
         Removes a disk from the list. You can remove a disk only if it's
            empty.

      @{b}Rename:@{ub}
         Renames a disk. See @{"Rename Disk window" link "WI_NameDisk" 0}.

      @{b}Update:@{ub}
         Delete the old (Deleted and eXpired) files from this disk and
            reads the free space on the disk to update it in the base.

      @{b}Convert Links:@{ub}
         When you click on this button, PDBase searches for all programs,
            if there are link files (LINKs) that belong to the selected
            disk. If there are some, they are converted to "normal" files,
            i.e, files handled by PDBase. See @{"Tricks" link "Tricks" 0} for
            example of usage.


   @{i}Right Listview:@{ui}

      @{b}Listview:@{ub}
         Displays the list of files on the selected disk. This list has two
         columns:
            column 1: name of the file.
            column 2: size of the file.

         Furthermore,
            * a "D" in front of a file shows that this file is marked for
               deletion, i.e it will be deleted as soon as possible.

            * a "X" in front of a file shows that this file is eXpired, i.e
               it belonged to a deleted program. This file will be deleted as
               soon as possible.

      @{b}Restore file:@{ub}
         Restores the selected files.
         Note: an eXpired file can't be restored, as it doesn't belong to any
            program anymore.

@endnode

@node "WI_NameDisk" "Rename disk window"
@toc "Reference"

   This window lets you rename a disk.

   @{b}Name:@{ub}
      Name of the disk.

   @{b}Really apply to disk:@{ub}
      If this button is checked, the disk will really be renamed. If not,
         you'll have to rename the disk yourself.
@endnode

@node "Menu_Project" "Project Menu"
@toc "Reference"

   @{b}New:@{ub}
      Clears current database to start a new project.

   @{b}Open:@{ub}
      Opens a disk based database.

   @{b}Save:@{ub}
      Saves the database on disk with the current name.
      (current name is set by successfull "Open" or "Save As")

   @{b}Save As:@{ub}
      Saves the database on disk but asks a file name first.

   @{b}Save as ASCII:@{ub}
      Creates an ASCII (readable text) dump of the current category.

   @{b}About:@{ub}
      Information about PDBase.

   @{b}Quit:@{ub}
      Quit PDBase. If database is not saved, opens a requester first to
         save database.
@endnode

@node "Menu_Settings" "Settings Menu"
@toc "Reference"

   @{b}Create Icons?:@{ub}
      If this menu is selected, an icon will be created when a base is saved.
         Note: if the base has already an icon, it won't be overwritten.
         The icon used is:
         ENV:PDBase/def_PDBase.info, then ENV:sys/def_PDBase.info, then
         the default project icon.

   @{b}Copy comment:@{ub}
      If this menu is selected, when a file is copied, its comment is copied
         too. Otherwise, an empty comment is used.

   @{b}Copy date:@{ub}
      If this menu is selected, when a file is copied, its date is copied
         too. Otherwise, the date of the copied file is the current date.

   @{b}Save Settings:@{ub}
      Save the settings to the disk.
@endnode

@node "Menu_Edit" "Edit Menu"
@toc "Reference"

   @{b}Disks:@{ub}
      Opens the @{"Edit Disks window" link "WI_EditDisks" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Tricks" "Tricks"

   Here are some special situations that PDBase can handle:

   @{" You've already got archive disks " link "Trick_ReArchive" 0}
@endnode

@node "Trick_ReArchive" "You've already got archive disks"
@toc "Tricks"

   If you have already tried to maintain archive disks yourself or with
another program, you can keep this disks. The conversion to PDBase will just
need a little work.

   1) On your archive disks, put all the files in the root directory.

   2) @{"Create" link "CreateCat" 0} your categories.

   3) Add your programs.
      Let's say you want to add @{"ReOrg" link "Copy_ReOrg" 0} to you database and @{"ReOrg" link "Copy_ReOrg" 0} is already
      archived on disk "DSK64" as two files: reorg31.lha and
reorg311pch.lha.

      Click on "Add Program". The @{"program window" link "WI_Prog" 0} opens. Complete the
      string gadgets (name, version, comment) and add the two files with
      @{b}"Add Link"@{ub} gadget. Then click on OK.

      Repeat the same operation for all your programs.

   4) Go in the @{"Edit Disks window" link "WI_EditDisks" 0} and for each of your disks:

      * add the disk to the database with "Add" button.
      * click on "Convert Links" for this disk.

   That's all !
@endnode

