@node "ToDo" "To Do"

   I said in PDBase 1.2a that it would probaby be the last minor update...
      Well, I lied! 8^)))

   I actually released PDBase 1.2b, because I was unhappy with some minor
      details in version 1.2a. These details are now fixed.
   Furthermore, PDBase 1.0 was uploaded to aminet one year ago, so for PDBase
      first birthday, I though it would be funny to release a new version.


   Let's now speak of the real future of PDBase: the next release will be a
      major update.

   PDBase 2.0 is now fully designed, and I started its coding a few weeks ago.
      I think you can expect it in about two months (I don't promise anything
      though).

   Main features are:

    - a complete new GUI, featuring Drag&Drop everywhere.
    - a real and powerful support for read only media (CD-ROM).
    - a dedicated support for storing files on disks with subdirectories
        (mainly useful with large disks, as Syquest or ZIP).
    - a real database management, i.e you no longer need to 'Save' after
        editing. PDBase will directly write the modifications to the
        database in real time.
    - the disk swapping involved in copying and deleting files to/from
        several disks will be reduced again.
@endnode

